Devilled Eggs

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Eggs
	•	2 large eggs

Filling
	•	2 tablespoons (30 g) full-fat mayonnaise
	•	1 teaspoon (5 g) Dijon mustard
	•	1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt
	•	Pinch white pepper

Paprika Oil Finish
	•	1 teaspoon (5 ml) extra-virgin olive oil
	•	1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika

⸻

Method
	1.	Cook Eggs
Place eggs in a saucepan, cover with cold water by ~2 cm, and bring to a full boil.
Cover, remove from heat, and rest in hot water for 10 minutes.
	2.	Cool & Peel
Transfer eggs to ice water for 3 minutes. Peel cleanly.
	3.	Prepare Yolks
Halve eggs lengthwise. Remove yolks to a bowl; set whites aside.
	4.	Bloom Paprika Oil
Gently warm olive oil in a small pan over low heat. Add smoked paprika and heat 30 seconds until fragrant. Do not darken.
	5.	Make Filling
Mash yolks with mayonnaise, mustard, salt, white pepper, and half of the paprika oil until completely smooth and silky.
	6.	Fill & Finish
Spoon or pipe filling into egg whites. Drizzle lightly with remaining paprika oil.
Chill 5 minutes before serving for best texture.

⸻

Optional Enhancements
	•	Finely chopped chives or microgreens (freshness and color)
	•	A few drops of sherry vinegar or lemon juice (brighter finish)
	•	Substitute olive-oil aioli for mayonnaise (dairy-free)
	•	Use sweet paprika if smoked is unavailable (less depth)